e it. New tests are added covering the explain functionality.\\n\\n**Changed files:**\\n- cmd/entire/cli/explain.go (55 lines changed - refactored to use efficient checkpoint reading)\\n- cmd/entire/cli/explain_test.go (265 lines added - new test coverage)\\n- cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go (43 lines added - new shared helper)\\n\\nPlease review thoroughly for:\\n- Correctness of the performance fix\\n- Edge cases and error handling\\n- Test coverage quality\\n- Code duplication concerns\\n- Adherence to project patterns (error handling, logging, etc.)\\n- Any regressions the changes might introduce\",\"agentId\":\"a4839c0729df1486a\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01KLEPXv9bBtDEni9Spb33Lf\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_018YEq89JQMX18C656ZeRC8a\",\"uuid\":\"7aece147-6c5f-4865-98ea-4adfd6ce0f16\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T23:56:47.403Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"7aece147-6c5f-4865-98ea-4adfd6ce0f16\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/explain-hang-performance\",\"sessionId\":\"fdb22724-2611-4b40-aad2-931a530ffe25\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"fix/explain-hang-performance\",\"slug\":\"witty-wandering-sun\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Task\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_018YEq89JQMX18C656ZeRC8a\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_018YEq89JQMX18C656ZeRC8a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T23:57:37.495Z\",\"uuid\":\"241bb91a-731f-44a4-babe-da7b2852e123\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"085efb10-db16-41b9-b150-620c78bbf364\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/explain-hang-performance\",\"sessionId\":\"fdb22724-2611-4b40-aad2-931a530ffe25\",\"version\":\"2.1.52\",\"gitBranch\":\"fix/explain-hang-performance\",\"slug\":\"witty-wandering-sun\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_018YEq89JQMX18C656ZeRC8a\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good, all tests pass. Now I have a thorough understanding of the changes. Let me compile the review.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Code Review: Fix `entire explain` Hanging on Repos with Many Checkpoints\\n\\n### Overall Assessment\\n\\nThis is a well-targeted performance fix. The root cause -- calling `ReadLatestSessionContent` per checkpoint in a loop, which reads and parses full multi-MB JSONL transcripts -- is correctly identified and the solution is sound. The code reads only the tiny `prompt.txt` file via O(1) tree lookups instead. The secondary optimization (`hasAnyChanges` replacing `hasCodeChanges` for temporary checkpoint filtering) is also a good improvement, switching from O(files) full tree diffs to O(1) hash comparisons.\\n\\nThe tests pass, the code is well-documented, and the approach integrates cleanly with existing patterns. I have a few issues to flag.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### What Was Done Well\\n\\n1. **Correct diagnosis**: The performance bottleneck was accurately identified -- `ReadLatestSessionContent` reads the full `CheckpointSummary` and then the full `SessionContent` (including multi-MB transcripts) for every single committed checkpoint during listing. Reading only `prompt.txt` is orders of magnitude cheaper.\\n\\n2. **Good layering**: The metadata branch tree is fetched once at the top of `getBranchCheckpoints` and reused for all checkpoint prompt lookups. This is the correct pattern.\\n\\n3. **Thorough documentation**: The new `hasAnyChanges` function, `convertTemporaryCheckpoint` comment update, and `ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` godoc all clearly explain the trade-offs being made.\\n\\n4. **Defensive fallback logic**: The new helper falls back to session `0` if the computed index doesn't exist, and returns empty string on any error, maintaining the best-effort pattern used throughout the codebase.\\n\\n5. **Good test coverage**: Four new tests covering the prompt reading from committed checkpoints, `hasAnyChanges` for first commits, metadata-only changes, and no-op tree changes.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Issues\\n\\n#### Important (Should Fix)\\n\\n**1. Missing `t.Parallel()` on new tests**\\n\\nAll four new test functions (`TestGetBranchCheckpoints_ReadsPromptFromCommittedCheckpoint`, `TestHasAnyChanges_FirstCommitReturnsTrue`, `TestHasAnyChanges_MetadataOnlyChangeReturnsTrue`, `TestHasAnyChanges_NoOpTreeChangeReturnsFalse`) do not call `t.Parallel()`.\\n\\nPer `CLAUDE.md`: \\\"Always use `t.Parallel()` in tests.\\\" The exception is tests that modify process-global state. These tests use `t.Chdir()` which IS listed as an exception, so this is actually acceptable -- but only because `t.Chdir()` is being used. However, I note that `t.Chdir()` was introduced in Go 1.24 and is actually safe to use with `t.Parallel()` in Go 1.24+ because it scopes the chdir to the test's goroutine. Since the project targets Go 1.25.x, these could potentially use `t.Parallel()`.\\n\\nThat said, looking at the surrounding tests in `explain_test.go`, the existing test `TestGetBranchCheckpoints_DefaultBranchFindsMergedCheckpoints` (line 3476) also uses `t.Chdir()` without `t.Parallel()`, so the new tests follow the established local pattern.\\n\\n**Verdict**: The non-parallel tests are consistent with the surrounding code. No change required, but worth noting that the `t.Chdir()` in Go 1.25 is goroutine-scoped and `t.Parallel()` could be added to all of these.\\n\\n**2. No unit test for `ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` in the strategy package**\\n\\nThe new shared helper at `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/explain-hang-performance/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` (line 544) is only tested indirectly via the integration-style `TestGetBranchCheckpoints_ReadsPromptFromCommittedCheckpoint` test. There is no direct unit test in the strategy package for this function. Consider adding a focused unit test that verifies:\\n- Single-session checkpoint (sessionCount=1) reads from `0/prompt.txt`\\n- Multi-session checkpoint (sessionCount=3) reads from `2/prompt.txt`\\n- Fallback when computed index doesn't exist (falls back to `0/`)\\n- Empty/missing prompt.txt returns empty string\\n- Empty tree returns empty string\\n\\nThis matters because the function has specific fallback logic (lines 559-564) that should be directly tested rather than only through the full `getBranchCheckpoints` flow.\\n\\n#### Suggestions (Nice to Have)\\n\\n**3. Potential code duplication between `ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` and `ReadSessionPromptFromTree`**\\n\\nThe new function at `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/explain-hang-performance/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:544` shares the core pattern with `ReadSessionPromptFromTree` at line 478: open a tree path, find `prompt.txt`, read contents, call `ExtractFirstPrompt`. The new function could potentially reuse `ReadSessionPromptFromTree` internally:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree(tree *object.Tree, cpID id.CheckpointID, sessionCount int) string {\\n    cpPath := cpID.Path()\\n    latestIndex := max(sessionCount-1, 0)\\n    sessionPath := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"%s/%d\\\", cpPath, latestIndex)\\n    \\n    prompt := ReadSessionPromptFromTree(tree, sessionPath)\\n    if prompt == \\\"\\\" && latestIndex > 0 {\\n        // Fall back to session 0\\n        prompt = ReadSessionPromptFromTree(tree, fmt.Sprintf(\\\"%s/0\\\", cpPath))\\n    }\\n    return prompt\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis would reduce duplication and leverage the existing tested helper. The current implementation is not bad, but the pattern of \\\"navigate to tree, find file, read contents, extract prompt\\\" is repeated.\\n\\n**4. The `hasAnyChanges` behavior change is a semantic relaxation worth flagging**\\n\\nThe switch from `hasCodeChanges` to `hasAnyChanges` in `convertTemporaryCheckpoint` means that metadata-only checkpoints (where only `.entire/` files changed) will now appear in the list view. Previously these were filtered out. The comment at lines 1085-1090 clearly explains this trade-off, which is good. However, this means users may see more checkpoints in the list than before. The comment says \\\"This trade-off is intentional for list-view performance\\\" which is well-documented.\\n\\nThis is not a bug, but worth ensuring that downstream consumers of `convertTemporaryCheckpoint` results (the UI rendering) handle the additional metadata-only entries gracefully. From the code, these entries flow into the `points` slice which is sorted and limited, so this seems safe.\\n\\n**5. The `metadataTree` variable's nil check could be pushed into the helper**\\n\\nAt line 956 in `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/explain-hang-performance/cmd/entire/cli/explain.go`:\\n```go\\nif metadataTree != nil {\\n    point.SessionPrompt = strategy.ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree(metadataTree, cpID, cpInfo.SessionCount)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe nil check could be moved inside `ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` to accept a `*object.Tree` that may be nil and return `\\\"\\\"` early. This would simplify call sites and make the function more defensive. However, this is a minor style preference and the current approach works fine.\\n\\n**6. `ReadAllSessionPromptsFromTree` reads the latest session from root level, not from numbered subdirectory**\\n\\nI noticed that the existing `ReadAllSessionPromptsFromTree` function at `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/.worktrees/explain-hang-performance/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:603` reads the most recent session prompt from `checkpointPath` (root level), while `WriteCommitted` stores ALL sessions in numbered subdirectories (0/, 1/, ...). The new `ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` correctly reads from the numbered subdirectory. This is a pre-existing inconsistency in `ReadAllSessionPromptsFromTree`, not introduced by this PR, but worth noting for a future fix.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Plan Alignment\\n\\nThe implementation aligns well with the stated requirements:\\n\\n1. **Extract a shared helper for reading committed checkpoint prompts efficiently** -- Done: `ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` in `strategy/common.go`.\\n2. **Refactor the explain command to avoid loading unnecessary data** -- Done: `getBranchCheckpoints` now uses tree lookups instead of `ReadLatestSessionContent`.\\n3. **Add proper test coverage** -- Done: 4 new test functions covering the core scenarios.\\n\\nNote: The PR description mentions `ReadCommittedCheckpointPrompts` as the helper name, but the actual implementation uses `ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree`. This is a cosmetic discrepancy in the description only.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\n| Category | Count |\\n|----------|-------|\\n| Critical | 0 |\\n| Important | 1 (missing direct unit test for the new shared helper) |\\n| Suggestions | 4 |\\n\\nThe fix is correct and well-implemented. The performance improvement (reading tiny `prompt.txt` files vs. full multi-MB transcripts) should completely resolve the hanging issue. The only action item I would recommend before merge is adding direct unit tests for `ReadLatestSessionPromptFromCommittedTree` to cover its fallback logic and edge cases. Everything else is a suggestion for future improvement.\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a4839c0729df1486a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 77713\\ntool_uses: 38\\nduration_ms: 870954</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"5b69eac7-2cc9-48d1-8b31-691621da98e9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T23:57:37.493Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"## Code Review Request\\n\\n**What was implemented:** Fix for `entire explain` command hanging on repos with many checkpoints. The fix optimizes checkpoint prompt reading by extracting a shared helper that reads from committed checkpoints directly instead of loading all temporary checkpoints, and refactors the e